      "writtenOn": "2026-04-13T20:13:02Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m asking for each type to be enumerated based on the device characteristics.  \"modbus\" is a protocol, not a device, and doesn\u0027t define how we talk to a device, so that means that the device type needs promoted to the type, and we need to only accept the properties that we need for that device.  In the majority of cases, I suspect most configs will be\n\n{\n   \"Type\": \"PhillipsPumpType\",\n   \"Name\": \"My pump name\",\n}\n\nwith no other properties, because the implementation just handles the rest of the implementation of the pump.  only the things that are DIFFERENT should be going in the config here.",
      "parentUuid": "5a5aefdc_0e366b26",
      "revId": "5f10432df651b3bfff575b33c2f9dbbcfab05c94",
